The paper discusses the challenges of model-based development for large, complex, and heterogeneous software systems, which suggests that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. The focus on distributed systems and compositional modeling suggests that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The mention of ultra-large systems and the need for appropriate methodologies suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The use of modeling and composition techniques suggests that it could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. Finally, the mention of effective development suggests that it could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category.
